---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import FormattedDate from '../components/FormattedDate.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const recentPosts = (await getCollection('blog'))
	.sort((a, b) => b.data.pubDate.valueOf() - a.data.pubDate.valueOf())
	.slice(0, 3);
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<link rel="preload" as="image" href="/cover.jpg" fetchpriority="high" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<div class="page-column">
			<div class="site-banner-wrap">
				<img class="site-banner" src="/cover.jpg" alt="Kingfisher of Baltiza" fetchpriority="high" loading="eager" />
			</div>

			<div class="home-layout">
				<main class="home-main">
					<p class="section-head">About Kingfisher</p>

					<p>
Welcome to the webpage of Kingfisher of Baltiza, and her skipper Meg Loftus.
</p>
<p>
Kingfisher is a 32ft William Atkin 'Eric' class yacht built in Malaysia in 1974. She is interestingly constructed, primarily in that she is built entirely of a rare Malaysian hardwood called Chengai, which has been described to be harder and heavier than teak. This, reinforced by batten-seamed planks and a full length internal ceiling, makes her a sturdy little vessel and she is showing remarkably little wear from 50 years of adventures.  
</p>
<p>
When I brought her in 2021, her laid Chengai deck had been leaking badly for a few years so she was looking a little down at heel. However further inspection revealed her solid construction and a very thorough refit in 2015, including a new beta 43 engine and full standing and running rigging. I sailed her home to Ullapool with my Dad Tim Loftus and the next spring we put a new plywood and fibreglass deck over the laid one in Johnson and Loftus Boatyard. She was now ready for cruising!
</p>
<p>
Since then we have sailed all over the Hebrides, made a circumnavigation of Ireland and even been up to the Lofoten Islands in Norway. She has proven herself to be a gentle and seaworthy vessel and has done an admirable job of looking after her young crew.  
</p>
<p>
Her sister ship is the well-known Suhali, sailed by Sir Robin Knox-Johnston in the first ever solo, non-stop circumnavigation of the globe in the 1968-1969 Sunday Times Golden Globe Race.
				</p>


					<hr />

					<div class="home-boxes">
						<div class="content-box">
							<h3>Greenland 2026</h3>
							<p>Preparation is in full swing for the KF's July expedition to Graah's Havn. Learn more about our attempt to climb here.</p>
							<a class="more-link" href="/greenland-2026">View expedition details &rarr;</a>
						</div>

						<div class="content-box">
							<h3>Blog</h3>
							<p>Follow for updates on the general whereabouts of Kingfisher.</p>
							<a class="more-link" href="/blog">Browse all posts &rarr;</a>
						</div>

						<div class="content-box">
							<h3>Gallery</h3>
							<p>Photos from time aboard Kingfisher.</p>
							<a class="more-link" href="/gallery">Browse photos &rarr;</a>
						</div>

					</div>
				</main>

				<aside class="home-sidebar">
					<p class="section-head">Recent Updates</p>
					{recentPosts.map((post) => (
						<div class="recent-post">
							<a href={`/blog/${post.id}/`}>{post.data.title}</a>
							<span class="recent-date"><FormattedDate date={post.data.pubDate} /></span>
						</div>
					))}
					<a class="more-link" style="display:block; margin-top: 0.75rem;" href="/blog">All posts &rarr;</a>
				</aside>
			</div>
		</div><!-- /.page-column -->

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.home-layout {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 220px;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		padding: 1rem;
		align-items: start;
	}

	.home-main { min-width: 0; }

	.home-boxes {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.home-sidebar {
		border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
		padding-left: 1rem;
	}

	.recent-post {
		padding: 0.5rem 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
	}

	.recent-post a {
		display: block;
		font-weight: bold;
		font-size: 0.85em;
		text-decoration: none;
		color: var(--link);
	}

	.recent-post a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	.recent-date {
		display: block;
		font-size: 0.75em;
		color: var(--text-dim);
		margin-top: 0.1rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 700px) {
		.home-layout {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
		.home-sidebar {
			border-left: none;
			border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
			padding-left: 0;
			padding-top: 1rem;
		}
		.home-boxes {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
